AttributeSubGroup.AttributeDescription: Scenario specification - changing fisheries conditions over time

Attribute.AttributeDescription: Changes in selectivity through time
Arrays to indicate when each change in selectivity begins (days from run start). There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in selectivity for that fishery

Arrays to indicate new form of the selectivity for that group. select curve: 0=const, 1=logistic, 2=norm, 3=lognorm, 4=gamma. There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in selectivity for that group.

Arrays to indicate change in lsm of selectivity curve for each change in selectivity for the fishery. If a constant selectivity is being used than this parameter indicates the change in this constant value. There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in selectivity for that group.

Arrays to indicate change in sigma of selectivity curve for each change in selectivity for the fishery. There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in selectivity for that group.
Change in fisheries coverage through time
Arrays to indicate when each change in fishing coverage begins (days from run start). There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in fishing coverage for that fishery.
Arrays to indicate time period over which change in fishing coverage occurs (days). There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in fishing coverage for that fishery.

Arrays to indicate proportional change in fishing coverage (relative to K_cover entered above). There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in fishing coverage for that fishery.

AttributeSubGroup.AttributeDescription: Changes in fishing gear swept area.

Attribute.AttributeDescription: number of changes in fishing gear swept area
Arrays to indicate when each change in swept area begins (days from run start). There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in swept area for that fishery.
Arrays to indicate time period over which change in swept area occurs (days). There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in swept area for that fishery.
Arrays to indicate proportional change in swept area (relative to swept_area entered above). There must be as many entries in this array as there are number of changes in swept area for that fishery.
Number of changes in discarding

Arrays to indicate when each change in discarding begins (days from run start). There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in discarding across all groups (e.g. if the highest number of changes in a single fishery by a single group is 6 then there must be 6 entries etc).

Arrays to indicate new minimum legal size limit for fishery. Its a multiplication factor relative to the original minimum size. There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in discarding for any group.

Arrays to indicate new proportion of undersize fish retained. Its a multiplication factor relative to the original proportion retained. There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in discarding for any group.

Arrays to indicate new level of discarding for that group. There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in discarding for any group. It a a multiplcation factor relative to the original level of discarding (if using constant rates) or wastes (guts/skin) disposed of (if using size based discarding).

Arrays to indicate new level of waste discarding for that group. There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in discarding for any group. It a a multiplcation factor relative to the original level of discarding of waste (guts/skin).
Number of changes of catchability

Arrays to indicate when each change in catchability begins (days from run start). There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in catchability across all groups (e.g. if the highest number of changes for a single fishery by a single group is 6 then there must be 6 entries etc).
Arrays to indicate period over which change in catchability occurs (days). There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in catchability across all groups.

Arrays to indicate new level of catchability for that group. It a a multiplication factor relative to the original level of catchability. There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in catchability across all groups.

AttributeSubGroup.AttributeDescription: Changes in fishing mortality through time

Attribute.AttributeDescription: Number of changes of fishing mortality

Arrays to indicate when each change in fishing mortality begins (days from run start). There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in fishing mortality across all groups (e.g. if the highest number of changes for a single fishery by a single group is 6 then there must be 6 entries etc).
Arrays to indicate period over which change in fishing mortality occurs (days). There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in fishing mortality across all groups.

Arrays to indicate new level of fishing mortality for that group. It a a multiplication factor relative to the original level of fishing mortality. There must be as many entries in this array as the MAXIMUM number of changes in fishing mortality across all groups.
